flowchart TD
    A[Start of turn loop] --> B[Select current player]
    B --> C{Is player eliminated}
    C -->|Yes| D[Advance to next player] --> B

    C -->|No| E{Skip count > 0}
    E -->|Yes| F[Consume skip] --> D

    E -->|No| G{Is player in Jail}

    %%Jail branch
    G -->|Yes| J1[Attempt to leave Jail]
    J1 --> J2{Has Get Out of Jail Free card}
    J2 -->|Yes| J3[Use card and leave Jail]
    J3 --> H[Roll dice normally]

    J2 -->|No| J4{Player chooses to pay fine}
    J4 -->|Yes| J5[Pay fine to leave Jail]
    J5 --> H

    J4 -->|No| J6[Roll dice attempt]
    J6 --> J7{Rolled doubles?}

    J7 -->|Yes| J8[Leave Jail and move]
    J8 --> I[Resolve landing]

    J7 -->|No| J9[Remain in Jail]
    J9 --> J10{Have 3 failed attempts?}
    J10 -->|Yes| J11[Forced to pay fine, leave Jail]
    J11 --> H
    J10 -->|No| D

    %%Regular branch
    G -->|No| H[Roll dice and move player]
    H --> I[Resolve landing, cards, rent, etc.]

    I --> J{Did player earn extra turn?}
    J -->|Yes| A
    J -->|No| D

    %%Reasons for a skip turn
    subgraph SkipEffects [When skips occur]
        S1[Card says skip next turn] --> S2[Increase skip count for that player]
        S3[Player sent to jail] --> S2
        S4[Other penalties that skip turns] --> S2
    end